      "system": {
        "actionType": {
          "value": "reaction"
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature begins its turn in the fog</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The fog surges with energy, dealing @Damage[(6d10+27)[bludgeoning]] damage to all creatures in the fog as it harmfully mutates their bodies. Creatures in the area must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:32] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage. It resists mutation.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage. Its flesh becomes coated in foul-smelling blisters for 1 hour. For as long as it has this mutation, it is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 1} and can't reduce the value of its sickened condition.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage. Its limbs become painfully twisted for [[/gmr 1d4 #hours]]{1d4 hours}. For as long as it has this mutation, it is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 2} and can't reduce the value of its sickened condition.</p>",
